{[show NS]
[ROLE leader][STAGE pre-lead]
Lead the \HK. \HKQJ976 carries the solid king-queen-jack sequence, so lead the top of the sequence — the king.

[ROLE declarer][STAGE auction-end]
You are in 3\N. On top you have 2 \S, 1 \H (the lone ace), 2 \D and 2 \C — seven, with more to come. West is marked with the long, strong \H over your single \HA and no apparent entry, so West is the hand to shut out. Hold up the \HA, then develop \C for four tricks and \D for the rest, where every loser goes to safe East. Avoid the \S finesse completely — it loses to the danger hand.

[ROLE declarer][STAGE post-lead]
West led the \HK, top of a sequence, so West holds the \HQJ and a long suit ready to run. Duck the \H to cut East off from West's hand. Then develop \C for four tricks and take two \D, leading toward your honours so any loser falls to East, the safe hand. Two \S, one \H, two \D and four \C make nine. Don't be tempted by the \S finesse: it loses to West's \SQ and the \H pour out, so the \C are your safe ninth-trick source.

