[ROLE declarer][STAGE post-lead] West led the \H4, which looks like a fourth-best, suggesting about five \H and the missing honours behind your ace. By the rule of eleven, only one card higher than the four sits outside your hand and dummy, so East rates to hold at most a single high \H — the long, strong hearts rate to sit with West, the danger hand. Win or hold up to cut East off, then develop \D and \C, leading toward your honours so any losing finesse runs into East, the safe hand. Leave \S alone beyond the two top winners — the \S finesse loses to West and lets the \H cash.

