[PLAY 6 S \CT]
You have cashed your top \S and \D winners; now a low \C is led from dummy toward your hand, where you hold \CAT with the \CQ still out. East follows low. Which \C do you play?
[WHY]
Play the \CT - the finesse. The \CQ rates to sit with East, over your \CAT and under dummy's \CKJ87, so the ten forces it out or wins; and even on a loss it loses to East, the safe hand who cannot reach West's \H. Crashing the \CA instead surrenders the finesse and lets the \CQ score a trick.}
